A phase is one coherent, reviewable, low-risk increment of the work item. It contains one or more
**iterations** (each ~1 PR). Iterations within a phase are sequential by default unless explicitly
parallelizable.

If a constraint or blocker forces this phase's shape to change, update this file in place and
append a diary entry naming what changed and why. Don't delete the old shape silently.

